</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9936DCFF88E16D7CD8F89B17FDF80D" blockId="1.[136,1452,1799,1970]" pageId="1" pageNumber="166">
The type specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF88E16D7DC2F89411FEF89D" box="[402,640,1800,1825]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="1" pageNumber="166" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="inopinata">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF88E16D7DC2F89411FEF89D" box="[402,640,1800,1825]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="166">Pertusaria inopinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by a hardly rimose, dark grey to olive-greenish, not areolated thallus, with numerous irregular, rounded, 
<quantity id="4CDE9B39FF88E16D7E88F8B71021F8FA" box="[728,863,1835,1862]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="166" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 mm</quantity>
wide, grey-whitish to olive-greenish soralia (
<figureCitation id="131D2A59FF88E16D7930F8B713EBF8D5" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,234,1731,1753]" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lectotype of Pertusaria inopinata in HBG." pageId="1" pageNumber="166">Figure 1</figureCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF88E16D7D1FF8D3117BF8D6" author="Erichsen, C. F. E." box="[335,517,1871,1898]" pageId="1" pageNumber="166" pagination="77 - 101" refId="ref2989" refString="Erichsen, C. F. E. (1936) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Flechtengattung Pertusaria. Feddes Repertorium 41: 77 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / fedr. 19360410105" type="journal article" year="1936">Erichsen (1936)</bibRefCitation>
the thallus reacts P+ yellow, K+ yellow, C–and I–. Norstictic acid and traces of lecanoric and gyrophoric acids were detected by own chemical analyses. This name was reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F331764CFF88E16D7913F8EF16D5F831" box="[1347,1451,1907,1933]" name="Denmark" pageId="1" pageNumber="166">Denmark</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF88E16D7CC0F80B12D0F80D" author="Sochting, U. &amp; Alstrup, V." box="[144,430,1943,1969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="166" refId="ref4100" refString="Sochting, U. &amp; Alstrup, V. (2002) Danish lichen checklist. Ver. 2. Botanical Institute, University of Copenhagen, Copenhagen." type="book" year="2002">Søchting &amp; Alstrup 2002</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F331764CFF88E16D7D91F80B1157F80D" box="[449,553,1943,1969]" name="Germany" pageId="1" pageNumber="166">Germany</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF88E16D7E68F80B11A2F80E" author="Erichsen, C. F. E." box="[568,732,1943,1970]" pageId="1" pageNumber="166" pagination="77 - 101" refId="ref2989" refString="Erichsen, C. F. E. (1936) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Flechtengattung Pertusaria. Feddes Repertorium 41: 77 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / fedr. 19360410105" type="journal article" year="1936">Erichsen 1936</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F331764CFF88E16D7F4BF80B1017F80D" box="[795,873,1943,1969]" name="Poland" pageId="1" pageNumber="166">Poland</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF88E16D7F27F80B1708F80D" author="Alstrup, V. &amp; Olech, M." box="[887,1142,1943,1969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="166" pagination="185 - 206" refId="ref2418" refString="Alstrup, V. &amp; Olech, M. (1992) Checklist of the lichens of the Tatra National Park, Poland. Zeszyty Naukowe Uniwersytetu Jagiellonskiego, Prace botaniczne 24: 185 - 206." type="journal article" year="1992">Alstrup &amp; Olech 1992</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF596654FF8BE16E7CD8FBEC11F3FB39" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423925" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5423925" box="[136,653,1136,1158]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423925/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" startId="2.[136,234,1136,1158]" targetBox="[151,1436,190,1112]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8B9936DCFF8BE16E7CD8FBEC11F3FB39" blockId="2.[136,653,1136,1158]" box="[136,653,1136,1158]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8BE16E7CD8FBEC127DFB39" bold="true" box="[136,259,1136,1158]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
Lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8BE16E7DD8FBED114BFB3A" box="[392,565,1137,1158]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="jurana">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8BE16E7DD8FBED114BFB3A" box="[392,565,1137,1158]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">Pertusaria jurana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in HBG.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9936DCFF8BE16E7CEDFB281104FAAB" blockId="2.[136,1452,1204,1663]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">
The type of 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8BE16E7D15FB291150FB72" box="[325,558,1205,1230]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="inopinata">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8BE16E7D15FB291150FB72" box="[325,558,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">Pertusaria inopinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically and chemically concordant with 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8BE16E782BFB29120DFB4E" authority="(Nylander 1885: 296) Hafellner" authorityName="Hafellner" baseAuthorityName="Nylander" baseAuthorityPageNumber="296" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Lepra" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="excludens">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8BE16E782BFB29164DFB72" box="[1147,1331,1204,1230]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">Lepra excludens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8BE16E7911FB281384FB4F" author="Nylander, W." pageId="2" pageNumber="167" pagination="295 - 301" refId="ref3514" refString="Nylander, W. (1885) Addenda nova ad Lichenographiam europaeam. Contin. XLIV. Flora 68 (15): 295 - 301." type="journal article" year="1885">Nylander 1885: 296</bibRefCitation>
) Hafellner
</taxonomicName>
, in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8BE16E7DC9FB44119DFB4F" author="Hafellner, J. &amp; Turk, R." box="[409,739,1240,1267]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" pagination="1 - 216" refId="ref3105" refString="Hafellner, J. &amp; Turk, R. (2016) Die lichenisierten Pilze Osterreichs-eine neue Checkliste der bisher nachgewiesenen Taxa mit Angaben zur Verbreitung und Substratokologie. Stapfia 104 (1): 1 - 216." type="journal article" year="2016">
Hafellner &amp; 
<collectingCountry id="F331764CFF8BE16E7E74FB441124FB4E" box="[548,602,1240,1266]" name="Turks and Caicos Islands" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">Türk</collectingCountry>
(2016: 172)
</bibRefCitation>
(syn. 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8BE16E7F77FB451730FB4F" authority="Nyl." authorityName="Nyl." box="[807,1102,1240,1267]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="excludens">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8BE16E7F77FB45176DFB4E" box="[807,1043,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">Pertusaria excludens</emphasis>
Nyl.
</taxonomicName>
). Therefore 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8BE16E7885FB451624FB4E" box="[1237,1370,1241,1266]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="inopinata">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8BE16E7885FB451624FB4E" box="[1237,1370,1241,1266]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">P. inopinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8BE16E7DB8FB61110DFAAA" box="[488,627,1276,1303]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="excludens">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8BE16E7DB8FB611286FAAA" box="[488,504,1277,1302]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8BE16E7E55FB60110DFAAA" box="[517,627,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">excludens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9936DCFF8BE16E7CEDFABC179AFA52" blockId="2.[136,1452,1204,1663]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">
During herbarium studies three original specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8BE16E7F40FABD10E9FA86" box="[784,919,1313,1338]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="inopinata">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8BE16E7F40FABD10E9FA86" box="[784,919,1313,1338]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">P. inopinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found in 
<collectionCode id="ED37AE19FF8BE16E7811FABD1701FA87" box="[1089,1151,1313,1339]" country="Japan" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/fv5j-intd" name="Hiroshima Botanical Garden" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">HBG</collectionCode>
, one collected by Erichsen and annotated as ‘Typus’ consists of two pieces of stone with the same thallus (
<figureCitation id="131D2A59FF8BE16E7FAFFAD81720FAE3" box="[1023,1118,1348,1375]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,234,1731,1753]" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lectotype of Pertusaria inopinata in HBG." pageId="2" pageNumber="167">Figure 1</figureCitation>
). The other two were cited in the protologue, but collected by Lettau and Schade. All samples studied correspond in morphological and anatomical characters with the description provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8BE16E7E23FA101054FA1B" author="Erichsen, C. F. E." box="[627,810,1420,1447]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" pagination="77 - 101" refId="ref2989" refString="Erichsen, C. F. E. (1936) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Flechtengattung Pertusaria. Feddes Repertorium 41: 77 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / fedr. 19360410105" type="journal article" year="1936">Erichsen (1936)</bibRefCitation>
. The chemistry of the 
<typeStatus id="549D887EFF8BE16E7874FA11172AFA1B" box="[1060,1108,1421,1447]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">type</typeStatus>
specimen annotated as ‘typus’ and other samples were checked by P. James and norstictic acid and traces of lecanoric and gyrophoric acid were detected (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8BE16E7CA4FA4812FDFA53" author="Hanko, B." box="[244,387,1492,1519]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" pagination="1 - 297" refId="ref3144" refString="Hanko, B. (1983) Die Chemotypen der Flechtengattung Pertusaria in Europa. Bibliotheca Lichenologic 19: 1 - 297." type="journal article" year="1983">Hanko 1983</bibRefCitation>
). The presence of these secondary metabolites is confirmed by own research.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9936DCFF8BE16E7CEDFA6411FDF9C3" blockId="2.[136,1452,1204,1663]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8BE16E7CEDFA641227F9AF" author="Hanko, B." box="[189,345,1528,1555]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" pagination="1 - 297" refId="ref3144" refString="Hanko, B. (1983) Die Chemotypen der Flechtengattung Pertusaria in Europa. Bibliotheca Lichenologic 19: 1 - 297." type="journal article" year="1983">Hanko (1983)</bibRefCitation>
cited as a ‘typus’ the specimen collected by Schade (“ 
<collectingCountry id="F331764CFF8BE16E7FE5FA651089F9AF" box="[949,1015,1529,1555]" name="Germany" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">DDR</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingRegion id="49E2F83EFF8BE16E7851FA64171FF9AE" box="[1025,1121,1528,1554]" country="Germany" name="Sachsen" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">Sachsen</collectingRegion>
: Leusitzer Niederung 7.1936, Schade, HBG-1213”), but the data presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8BE16E7EE5F98010F0F98B" author="Hanko, B." box="[693,910,1564,1591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" pagination="1 - 297" refId="ref3144" refString="Hanko, B. (1983) Die Chemotypen der Flechtengattung Pertusaria in Europa. Bibliotheca Lichenologic 19: 1 - 297." type="journal article" year="1983">Hanko (1983: 201)</bibRefCitation>
do not match those given in the protologue by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8BE16E7CD8F9DC1216F9E7" author="Erichsen, C. F. E." box="[136,360,1600,1627]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" pagination="77 - 101" refId="ref2989" refString="Erichsen, C. F. E. (1936) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Flechtengattung Pertusaria. Feddes Repertorium 41: 77 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / fedr. 19360410105" type="journal article" year="1936">Erichsen (1936: 99)</bibRefCitation>
, therefore, his typification cannot be considered effective, and consequently, a new 
<typeStatus id="549D887EFF8BE16E7959F9DC160EF9E6" box="[1289,1392,1600,1626]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D5FFF8BE16E79C3F9DD138DF9C2" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="inopinata">
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8BE16E79C3F9DD16DAF9E6" box="[1427,1444,1601,1626]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8BE16E7CD8F9F9138DF9C2" box="[136,243,1637,1662]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">inopinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is designated (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B2DFF8BE16E7DCAF9F81109F9C3" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[410,631,1636,1663]" pageId="2" pageNumber="167" pagination="159" refId="ref4129" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="journal article" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="B952EACEFF8BE16E7DABF9F9114DF9C2" box="[507,563,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
